The paper proposes a novel image hashing method for nearest neighbor retrieval tasks using deep learning-based techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on optimizing the discrete binary codes, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of deep learning techniques also suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with image retrieval, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a method that considers rich semantic information, which is related to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
